## OUTPUT FORMAT
{{.OutputFormatSnippet}}
{{- if .OutputSchemaSnippet}}
- `id`, `verdict`, `priority`, `confidence_score`, and `remarks` are TOP-LEVEL keys of the JSON object; do NOT wrap them in a `verification` object
- `id` is the same UUID as the input `finding.id`; copy that actual UUID, never the `<uuid-v4>` placeholder
- `verdict` is one of `confirmed`, `refuted`, `unverified`
- `priority` is an integer 0-3
- `confidence_score` is a number between 0 and 1 expressing your confidence in the verdict
- `remarks` is a short markdown explanation of the verdict; when `refuted` because an actual issue claim is false, MUST cite the concrete code or invariant that contradicts the finding
  - when `refuted` because the input is a non-finding, `remarks` MUST be exactly "no issue"
  - add paragraphs, e.g. an empty line, between distinct points to improve readability
  - put code references and symbol names in backticks or code blocks
  - format bold or italic when it makes sense to emphasize a point
